Standardize
References

https://maristie.com/blog/differences-between-normalization-standardization-and-regularization/

Definition
Standardization rescales data to have a mean (&#x1D707;) of 0 and standard deviation (&#x1D70E;) of 1 (unit variance).
X&#x2032;=X&#x2212;&#x3BC;&#x3C3;
X&apos; = \frac{X - \mu}{\sigma}
X&#x2032;=&#x3C3;X&#x2212;&#x3BC;&#x200B;
def standardize(X):
    X_std = X
    mean = X.mean(axis=0)
    std = X.std(axis=0)
    for col in range(np.shape(X)[1]):
        if std[col]:
            X_std[:, col] = (X_std[:, col] - mean[col]) / std[col]
    return X_std

